  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "E. coli synthesizes all 20 amino acids from central metabolic intermediates. Major biosynthetic families include: glutamate family (Glu, Gln, Pro, Arg) from \u03b1-ketoglutarate; aspartate family (Asp, Asn, Met, Thr, Ile, Lys) from oxaloacetate; serine family (Ser, Gly, Cys) from 3-phosphoglycerate; aromatic family (Phe, Tyr, Trp) from PEP + E4P via shikimate; pyruvate family (Ala, Val, Leu) from pyruvate; and histidine from PRPP. Each pathway has 2-12 enzymatic steps with feedback inhibition by end products.",
  "id": "ecoli_amino_acid_biosynthesis",
  "keywords": [
    "amino acid biosynthesis",
    "glutamate family",
    "aspartate family",
    "aromatic amino acids",
    "shikimate pathway"
  ],
